1 AN ACT concerning the department of administration; relating to the
2 procurement of managed care organizations for the Kansas program of
3 medical assistance; requiring adoption of policies.
4
5 Be it enacted by the Legislature of the State of Kansas:
6 Section 1. (a) The department of administration shall adopt written
7 policies governing the negotiated procurement of state medicaid services
8 to be provided by manged managed care organizations pursuant to a
9 contract with the Kansas program of medical assistance governed by
10 K.S.A. 75-37,102, and amendments thereto.
11 (b) Such policy shall include:
12 (1) A prohibition on destruction of records, including evaluation
13 documents, that complies with the Kansas open records act;
14 (2) adoption of a tiebreak procedure if part of the evaluation process
15 used to make award recommendations involves scoring by individuals or
16 committees; and
17 (3) a requirement to be transparent with the legislature during each
18 step of the procurement process to the fullest extent permitted by state
19 law; and
20 (4) an appeals process. Appeals shall be overseen and adjudicated
21 by an appeals committee. Such committee shall be comprised of the
22 president of the senate, the chairperson and ranking minority member
23 of the senate standing committee on financial institutions and
24 insurance, the chairperson and ranking minority member of the
25 senate standing committee on public health and welfare, the speaker
26 of the house of representatives, the chairperson and ranking minority
27 member of the house standing committee on insurance and the
28 chairperson and ranking minority member of the house standing
29 committee on health and human services. Such appeals committee
30 shall oversee and adjudicate appeals pursuant to this section in
31 accordance with policies adopted by the department of
32 administration.
33 (c) Policies required by this section shall be adopted and implemented

